    <section>
      <title>Shafting and propellor</title>

      <para>The output of the vessel's gearbox is coupled to the propellor
      shaft by a flexible coupling which reduces vibration and eliminates the
      need for precise engine alignment. The propellor shaft exits the vessel
      through a conventional stuffing-box with automatic shaft
      lubrication.</para>

      <section>
        <title>Anti-vibration coupling</title>

